  "body": "Ask for help. When geth runs to 1.1 million blocks, it is difficult to change and cannot be started\r\nWhen geth runs to 1.1 million blocks, it changes the fixed value of difficulty 18888, and it has been running for 2 months, reaching 6.5 million blocks. After restarting the node, it cannot start geth normally, and it rolls back to 1.1 million blocks, resulting in data loss.\r\nReward 3eth to solve this problem:\r\nrequirement:\r\n1. Use the backup image (6.5 million full block data) to resume normal startup and mining\r\n2. Other nodes can synchronize blocks\r\nthank you!",
